There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from Botswana. Medical evacuation flights remain possible. The Botswana authorities have also closed land border posts with neighbouring countries. Only citizens and residents will be allowed entry.
We know this is concerning for British people trying to leave Botswana. The British High Commission is in contact with airlines and local authorities to ensure British people can return to the UK from Botswana as soon as possible.
If you cannot leave Botswana at this time, see advice on staying in Botswana during coronavirus.
Future travel options
If you are a British national currently visiting Botswana and would like to return home to the UK, the British High Commission can update you when flight options become available by adding you to a mailing list. If you would like to receive these updates, email Gaborone.Enquiries@fco.gov.uk with the subject heading ‘return from Botswana’ and include your: name, mobile telephone number, location, and any other relevant information.
You should also sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British High Commission on Facebook and Twitter.
You will need to pay for your return travel to the UK. If departure options are available but you cannot afford the travel costs and have exhausted all other options for getting funds, you may be eligible to apply for an emergency loan from the government. This is a last resort option and you would need to repay the loan when you are back in the UK. For more information, contact Corporate Travel Management (CTM). CTM are a commercial partner of the FCO and are authorised to administer such loans on behalf of the FCO.
Your journey home
The National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) provides advice on how to stay safe as you travel by air.
When you arrive back in the UK, follow the guidance for when you return to the UK on steps you should take to protect yourself and others.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British High Commission from Monday to Friday from 8am-12pm on +267 761 290 42 and from 12pm-4pm on +267 760 299 41. Outside of these hours, please call +267 395 2841.
